\\ln t$ and one with $L(t)\\sim t^{1/\\sigma+1}$. All these\nregimes and their validity ranges have been found analytically and verified in\nnumerical simulations. Our results show that the main effect of the\nconservation law is a strong slowdown of COP dynamics if interactions have an\nextended range. Finally, we compare the Ising model at hand with continuum\napproaches based on a Ginzburg-Landau free energy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 16 Feb 2019 19:34:33 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 7 May 2019 10:58:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-06"}
